Binovation aims at solving the ongoing problems faced by the people during the pandemic by conducting a virtual techno-business competition, mainly involving Innovation and Business Model.
Click on KNOW MORE to explore the domains.
fields.details:
In the current light of the pandemic, BloomBox organized a virtual B-plan competition BINOVATION in August 2020. The Event was announced on 12th August, 2020 on various social media platforms and Dare2Compete website and registrations were started. The second event of BloomBox for this year witnessed a whopping 100+ registrations from around the country. For this event, 5 domains hit hard due to the pandemic caused by the Novel Coronavirus/Covid-19 were released on 15th August, namely Health, Agriculture, Entertainment, Education and Employment. The participating teams consisting of 1 to 4 members each were then sent a minimum of 2 problem statements in every domain through mail communication. The partners of the event were MILD who provided internships worth ₹5000 to every winning team member. Our second sponsorship partner was HEADSTART India who offered mentorship to the winning team helping them make their ideas a great success and making it ready for the real world along with special discounts to all participants on their mentorship programs. 

	The event consisted of 2 rounds where the teams had to send in their solutions in the form of pdfs for a particular problem statement for the first round. The top 10 teams from round 1 were shortlisted by the Binovation Planning Team and the results were announced on the official BloomBox website on 26th August, 2020. The winning teams had to present their ideas in the form of presentations to the above listed judges on 29th August, 2020 on Google Meets platform. The top 3 teams winning Binovation were announced by the judges on the same day and were posted on the website along with a feedback form on the very next day.

The Winning Teams were: 
1st Prize: Team Titans from KJSCE
2nd Prize: Team Arth from KJSCE
3rd Prize: Team Novus from XIME, Bangalore

fields.details:
BloomBox, E-Cell KJSCE in collaboration with E-Cell, SIMSR organized a B-plan workshop by the RedBull Basement University

The workshop was conducted by -
1. Mr. Romil Shah (A Business Analyst and a Headstarter)
2. Mr. Abhishek Barari (Head of Operations and Finance, MycuteOffice)

Mr. Romil Shah gave an overview of three waves of Entrepreneurs. The interactive discussion facilitated by Mr. Abhishek Barari included the concept of Lean Canvas which was demonstrated using a real life example which covered the problem statement, solutions to it, it’s feasibility, the customer segments correlating to the problem statement directly, key metrics, various channels to publicize, revenue systems, unique value propositions (UVP) and unfair advantages to the idea.

fields.details:
Brand Wars was one of the events of our E-Summit 2022.It was a two-day-long competition where participants competed with each other as bands but with a very interesting twist. Popular Brands were reimagined in starkly different domains and teams had to design an attractive poster and an effective marketing strategy for the same.
Students were asked to register as a Team of 1-4 members for the competition and it was kept open to all students from all colleges.
The problem Statements chosen were-
➢ Apple as cold drink brand.
➢ Harpic as a perfume company.
➢ McDonald’s as a fitness brand.
➢ Nykaa as a software brand.
We received a whopping 147 registrations from colleges all over the country.

The event was conducted in 2 rounds:
First Round (15th April 2022) –
1)The First Round of the Brand Wars was conducted via a Google Form of 2 Questions wherein the teams had to submit a google form consisting of the description of the problem statement and the poster for their brand.
2)The problem statements were revealed in the beginning of the competition and the teams had to choose a problem statement of their choice from the given problem statements and submit it via a google form. This entire selection of the problem statements was conducted in the beginning 15 minutes of the competition.
3) The teams had to submit the solution of Q1 i.e., the description of the problem statement within the next 45 minutes in the meet itself and solution of Q2 i.e., the poster for the same problem statement by evening 5 pm.
4) We received an incredible 67 submissions for Round 1 of Brand Wars.
5) The posters were added on a newly created Instagram page and the participants were allowed to promote the posts of their respective posters from 6pm to 12 pm to get as many likes and comments as possible.

The top two teams were selected from each problem statement so eight teams in total from 4 problem statements progressed to the final round.
The Prestigious judging panel for Round 2 of Brand Wars were:
1. Sangeeta Nagpure - Assistant Professor in Department of IT
2. Dipti Pawde - Assistant Professor in Department of IT

Round 2 (16th April 2022):
The round 2 began with introduction of all the top 8 teams as well as the respected judges. Top 2 teams from each problem statement were selected for the second round. Following the introduction, the teams began their presentation on the respective problem statements. It was an interactive session with QnA between the judges and teams. The teams too actively participated in the QnA Round. The judges scored the teams on the based on their Presentation and answers.
The winners of Brandwars Round 2:
1st Place: Team ACE
2nd Place: Team Passionates & Team Shadowhunters.

fields.description: As the grand finale of The Studentpreneur Series, BloomBox organized a Campus Company Panel Session. In this session, the panelists from various walks of life shared their student entrepreneurship journey with us. They enlightened the audience about the obstacles they faced and how they overcame them.
fields.details:
As a part of The Studentpreneur Series: a social media campaign celebrating and
fostering the spirit of Entrepreneurship wherein we brought to you some amazing facts
about Student Entrepreneurship, Campus Companies, Steps to start a Campus Company as
well as its numerous benefits throughout the month of July, BloomBox organized a the Campus
Company Panel Session as its grand culmination on 31st July 2021 at 5pm.

The Event was announced on 25th July, 2021 on various social media platforms like
WhatsApp, Instagram, LinkedIn and Facebook and registrations were started. This event of
BloomBox for the Studentpreneur Series witnessed a whopping 120+ registrations. 

Panelists for the session were :
Mr. Dhruman Gohil- Founder, Nurturing Lives
Ms. Heeral Dedhia- Founder LaunchIT 
Ms. Ruchira Joshi- Co-Founder,&Evolve, 
Mr. Akshat Kacheria: Founder ArchTech Venture | Currently pursuing MAM at London Business School
Mr. Abhishek Trivedi: Founder, Branding Catalyst (A former Campus Company Now Converted to Startup)

The panelists shared their journey, how their experience helped them to shape themselves, the challenges they faced, and how they overcame them by adapting. The session was concluded on a high note that there are various approaches to go out your Entrepreneurial journey and there is no single, ideal method of practicing Entrepreneurship.
Everyone has their own way of starting and running their own venture and Campus Company,
offered by our E-Cell to our college students is one of the guided and hassle-free ways to begin
and gain immense experience with minimal risk involved.

fields.details:
BloomBox, the E-cell of KJSCE organised Ennovate’20, a techno-business competition blending together both Entrepreneurship and Innovation with the aim ‘Make your work know it’s Worth!’.
BloomBox, the E-cell of KJSCE organised Ennovate’20, a techno-business competition blending together both Entrepreneurship and Innovation with the aim ‘Make your work know it’s Worth!’. The participants had to develop a prototype of the technical product for an innovative idea and also a business plan for their product.
Whether through developing an app, demonstrating the use of machine learning, developing hardware prototypes, developing helpful websites or working on open source technology, this challenge was for innovators who had to translate the Language of code into revolutionary solutions for real-world problems. Participants took away indelible knowledge by our judges and an astounding experience of participating in a techno-business competition.

fields.description: Absolute blend of Entrepreneurship, Innovation and Technology, where participants come together to innovate and mould their ideas to realistic solutions and progressive business plans.
fields.details:
Ennovate is an absolute blend of Entrepreneurship, Innovation and Technology, where students from every background can come together to innovate and mould their ideas to realistic solutions and progressive business plans.

Ennovate’19 is a Techno-Business event with a tagline ‘Make your work know its worth’. Participants are asked to build a prototype of website/ web application demonstrating the use of any technology and provide innovative solutions for real-world problems through their prototype. Along with the prototype, the teams are also asked to provide a business plan for their prototype.

Gaurang Shetty has been part of the startup ecosystem through RiiDL for some time now and he said that the students were fortunate enough to be in a campus where they have an incubator inside the campus so they can spend some time and learn, shadow there and see how their lives are like.

Statisitcs
1. Prize Money: 1st place – Rs. 7000 + Goodies.
2nd place – Rs. 5000
3rd place – Rs. 1500 + Goodies.
4th place – Rs.1500 + Goodies.
2. Number of Participants: Total 18 teams participated in the competition from colleges all over Mumbai with major participation from K.J. Somaiya College of Engineering.
3. Duration: The participants were given a time of 15-20 days to build their prototype. The event was held on 5th April 2019 in K.J. Somaiya College of Engineering.
4. Specifics:
Round 1 (Elimination Round) : 5th April 2019
The competition started with the elimination round. Each team were given 7 minutes (5 mins for presenting and 2 mins for Q&A) for Round 1 where they had to pitch their ideas through their prototype.
Round 2 (Final Round) : 5th April 2019
The top 8 selected teams were then given 12 minutes per team (7 mins for presentation and 5 mins for Q&A) for presentation. In this round, participants presented their problem statements, their respective solutions to it using technology and their business models.
5. Judges: Our highly recognized panel of judges for this event were -
1. Mr. Rohit Kilam (CIO/ CTO, Aditya Birla Finance Ltd.)
2. Mr. Neil Savant (Founder & CEO, NUOS Home Automation)
3. Mr. Raj Dhiravani (Incubation Manager, riidl)
4. Mr. Mehul Ved (Founder, Stratahive)
5. Ms. Avani Sakhapara (Assistant Professor, Department of Information Technology, KJSCE)
6. Ms. Sunayana Jadhav (Assistant Professor, Department of Information Technology, KJSCE)

fields.description: BloomBox organized its flagship event Ennovate as a part of the first ever E-Summit in KJSCE’s history. The idea behind this event was to give participants hands-on experience in the world of entrepreneurship.
fields.details:
BloomBox organized its flagship event Ennovate as a part of the first ever E-Summit in KJSCE’s history. The idea behind this event was to give participants hands-on experience in the world of entrepreneurship. Participants were given various domains like Fintech Solutions, Women Safety and Empowerment, Rural Area Development, HealthCare, IOT Solutions to daily life problems, Tech-based Solutions for Disabled, Agriculture Technology, Security and Surveillance Protection of private property, Sustainable Environment,Solar Cell Technology, Tackling fake information online, online data privacy, Open Innovation. Ennovate has always been a techno-business competition this year was no different. We focussed primarily on making our participants ready for the real world entrepreneurship challenges. 

Every business needs mentors to guide them through all the ups and downs so to make it more realistic we provided our participants with an excellent set of mentors consisting of Dr. Irfan Siddavatam - Head of Department, KJSCE, Prof. Ashwini Dalvi - Assistant Professor, KJSCE and Prof. Dipti Pawade Assistant Professor, KJSCE. These mentors helped participants build their business plan from 24th of March and out of those participants finalists were shortlisted on the 16th April and were asked to present their business plan in front of our very talented judges. The judges, Mr. Adnyesh Dalpati - a technologist and enterprise architect, Mr. Hariharan Mahadevan - an accomplished BFSI professional and Dr. Prashant Singhal - Founder of Cosmic Neurons. Participating teams came up with excellent ideas that were brainstormed by them and by the end of the final round we found our top four teams, two for the first and second prizes and the other two for Best business plan and best innovation plan respectively. Prizes worth INR 50,000 were distributed among these teams.

Statistics:
Prizes:

Second Prize - Worth INR 30,000

Number of Participants: 41 teams from all over the country participated in Global Blockchain Hackathon.
Duration of Event: 19th, 21st and 22nd December 2018.
Specifics:
19th December, 2018: Garage Session (Hands-on workshop on Blockchain Technology)
The Hackathon started with a Hands-on workshop on Blockchain Technology so that the students could clear their doubts and could understand more about Blockchain Technology. This workshop was held on 19th December to prepare the participants for the Hackathon.
19th December, 2018: Panel Discussion
A panel session on ‘Blockchain: The Future of Money, Governance and Law’ was organized to cover Blockchain Technology advertising implications to potential regulation to security concerns, its applications in the start-up world and its pitfall as well.
The panel was as follows -
1. Mr. Saurabh Ambwani (Blockchain Head, Larsen & Toubro Infotech Ltd.)
2. Mr. Ritesh Kakkad (Co-founder, XinFin).
3. Mr. Amol Dethe (Editor, FinBizness)
4. Mr. Prasanna Lohar (Head Innovation & Architecture, DCB Bank Ltd.)
Moderator - Ms. Nehha Wadhwa (Founder, The Pink Table).
21st December, 2018: Hackathon
The Global Blockchain Hackathon commenced at 11:30 AM on 21st December, 2018. 4 problem statements were given to the teams. They were free to choose and work on any one of the problem statements. It was a 24 hours hackathon.
22nd December, 2018: Evaluation of teams
The teams stayed back overnight and worked on their products. The evaluation of the teams was done to filter out 10 best teams for the pitching round.
22nd December, 2018: Pitching Session
The 10 teams were allotted time slots of 10 minutes each where they had to present their idea/ product and propose a business pitch to the judges. The criteria of judging was -
Innovation Deploy Ability Entrepreneurial Opportunity Presentation + Timing
The esteemed judges for the Hackathon were as follows:
Mr. Rohit Kilam (CIO/ CTO, Aditya Birla Finance Ltd.)
Mr. Prasham Rambhia (Assistant Vice President, Nomura)
Mr. Irfan Siddavatam (Assistant professor, Information Technology Department, KJSCE)
Mr Vineet Parikh (Co-founder, tradescrypt.com)
Mr. Chintan Ghelani (Co-founder, tradescrypt.com)
22nd December, 2018: Closing Ceremony and Announcement of Winners
After all the assessments, the closing ceremony was followed by a speaker session on ‘Business models in digital Era and Blockchain Technology’ by Mr Rohit Kilam. He spoke about various fields in which Blockchain can be diversely implemented. He passed on a very insightful message to our participants stating ‘Focus 99% on the problem and you will get your solution.’

Statisitcs
1. Cash Prize worth INR 15,000
2.Incubation Facility (RiiDL)
3.FabLab (RiiDL) membership worth INR 6,000
4.Two Months Internship Opportunity at VPS Techub Private Limited
5.Goodies & Gift Voucher from Facebook Developer Circle, Pizza Hut and many more
Round 1 (Elimination Round) : 5th April 2019
Specifics:
1. Speaker Session by Neil Savant (Founder & CEO, NUOS Home Automation) – 30th October 2018.
Topic: Internet of Things: A new growing field
A brief on the real world implementations of IoT and it's modules were given by Mr. Neil Savant. An insight on how having a start-up business is different from a corporate job was also given and a few challenges faced by budding startups were also addressed.
2. Hands on Workshop by Prof. Irfan Siddhavatam – 2nd November 2018.
Irfan Sir explained how to demonstrate a working IoT model. He also gave a brief idea about the judging criteria of the prototypes and some helpful insights on how the teams can make maximum utilization of 30 hours of the hackathon.
3. Speaker Session by Mr. Gaurang Shetty (Chief innovation catalyst and CEO, riidl) – 3rd November 2018.
Topic: How to deliver a business pitch
Mr. Gaurang Shetty gave detailed analysis of start-up community. He explained a few problems faced while launching a product and also how product market compatibility plays a crucial role in making it a success. He threw light on the aspects of a business pitch and how important it is to have a concise, crisp and self-explanatory tagline. He also spoke about elevator pitches and concluded the session by giving insights for an ideal product presentation and business pitch.
4. Hackathon – 3rd November 2018.
The teams were given their components and the Hackathon commenced at 12:30pm on 3rd November, 2018.
5. Submission of Prototypes – 4th November 2018.
The teams stayed back overnight and worked on the prototypes. At 6:30pm the Hackathon was over and the teams submitted their prototypes.

HULT Prize Somaiya Vidyavihar is the Campus Round for HULT Prize which is an annual competition that crowd-sources ideas from MBA and college students after challenging them to solve a pressing social issue around topics such as food security, water access, energy, and education. Former U.S. president Bill Clinton selects the challenge topic and announces the winner each September. 

HULT Prize 2020-21 was directed by Campus Director Shantanu Valdamani.  HULT Prize Somaiya Vidyavihar was organised by the E-Cells in Somaiya Vidyavihar Campus i.e. Pathfinder, E-Cell SIMSR, BloomBox, E-Cell KJSCE and  E-cell KJSSC.

The main motive of HULT Prize is to test the minds of young individuals to build them and make them ready for the entrepreneurial challenges. The HULT Prize 2021 challenge was 'Food for Good'.

The 10 teams presented their ideas in front of an amazing panel of judges which included Mr Gaurang Shetty, Chief Innovation Catalyst, Riidl & Founder of Maker Mela, Mr. Amitabh Vyas, National Scouting Lead, UnLtd India, Mr. Satish Kumar Gupta, Principal Assessor and Food & AYUSH Scheme Manager, Indian Register of Quality System (IRQS), Mr. Nilesh Lele, Founder and MD of Exelon Foodbio Advisors Pvt. Ltd.

fields.description: A 2-day design thinking competition where participants had to come up with innovative and feasible solutions for the given problem statements by BloomBox, the E-Cell of KJSCE.
fields.details:
As a part of the first ever E-Summit in the history of KJSCE, BloomBox organized a
design thinking and idea generation competition IDEATHON on 24th and 25th April 2021. The
Event was announced on 31st March, 2021 on various social media platforms like Instagram,
LinkedIn and Facebook and portals and websites like Dare2Compete, TownScript,
Thecollegefever, Knowafest, Eventbrite and Evvnt and registrations were started. This event of
BloomBox for the grand E-Summit witnessed a whopping 120+ registrations from around the
country. The participating teams consist of 1 to 3 members each. For Round 1, the participants
were given four day-to-day life problem statements with a time limit of 20 mins to brainstorm on
each of them, and 20 mins in the end for uploading their innovative and feasible solutions in a
Google form. The MS Teams platform used for Round 1 facilitated the feature of Breakout
Rooms: a meeting within the main meeting where each participating team could discuss their
solutions with complete privacy. The winning teams were awarded a total cash prize worth Rs.
1200 in addition to vouchers and winning certificates while all participating teams were given a
digital participation certificate for each team member.
The Round 1 of the event took place on 24th April, 2021 and the Final Round on 25th April,
2021. The top 7 teams from round 1 were shortlisted by the Ideathon Planning Team from a
raging participation of 36 teams on the day of the event and the results were announced via mail
on 24th April itself. The winning teams were judged on the basis of their investment pitch on any
one problem solution from Round 1 by 5 judges namely: Prof. Sagar Korde, Prof. Inderjit Singh
Dhanjal, Dr. Kashinath Patil, Mr. Mahesh Patil and Mr. Sandeep Parmar, who acted as potential
investors in their proposed idea, on Google Meet Platform. The top 3 teams winning Ideathon
were announced by the judges on the same day in the Closing Ceremony of the E-Summit and
were posted on the website along with a feedback form within the same week.

The panelists answered a variety of questions that our young entrepreneurs had in their minds and also shared stories of their invaluable experiences. fields.description: Plan-demic is aimed at finding business solutions to the probable post-pandemic problems in various sectors of business and life.
fields.details:

The event was announced on 3rd September 2021 on various social media platforms and registrations were started. The second event of BloomBox this year received over 80+ registrations from around the country. As people adapt to the new normal - "Life after Pandemic" they will face various problems in all sectors of work and life. We aimed to generate innovative entrepreneurial solutions for these problems through this competition. The aim was for the teams to ideate and come up with a feasible and viable business solution(Start-up Idea) to the given problem statements. Sectors of Focus were Education, Entertainment and Recreation, Jobs and Unemployment, Mental and Physical Health Care, Privacy and Information Security, Environment and Sustainability.
Students were asked to register as a Team of 1-4 members for the competition and it was kept open to all students from all colleges. The event consisted of 2 rounds where the teams had to send in their solutions in the form of pdfs for a particular problem statement for the first round. The top 7 teams from round 1 were shortlisted by the Plan-Demic Planning Team and the results were announced on our social media. The winning teams had to present their ideas in the form of presentations to the panel of judges on 18th September 2021 on Zoom platform. 
Our sponsors Ensemble, MILD, Mabb Infinity, EasyShiksha, Foxmula, LetsUpgrade, CertifyMe have played a key role in making the event successful and BloomBox is grateful to them for doing so. With the help of our sponsors, we had many prizes worth up to Rs. 30,000 for the winners as well as all our participants including Internships, Free Courses and Training, Free Workshops, and Discount Coupons.
The winners of the event were announced on the very same day by the judges and the session ended on a good note highlighting the fact that it doesn't matter whether it's a win or not the important lesson that everybody learned here was that we all can come together and innovate different solutions to a common problem, the diversity that our ideas present for a single cause is what keeps us united and humanity alive and by experience is how we learn.

fields.details:
Sociathon was this year's social event that was hosted in coordination with Enactus Somaiya Social cell. The goal of this event was to spread awareness and inquisitiveness about social entrepreneurship amongst the participants. This competition consisted of two rounds. The first round consisted of a speaker session followed by a presentation submission and a verbal pitch to the judges.

Round 1 - 15th April 2022
The Round 1 of Sociathon began with an informative and all-around speaker session conducted by Mr. Kuldeep Tripathi. The Session encompassed several technical aspects and concepts of Social Entrepreneurship such as cause identification, solution ideation, building a sustainable business model, reaching CSR/relevant investors, etc. as well as informed students about several strategies regarding implementation of projects/startups based on the model of social entrepreneurship.
Speaker Details: Mr.Kuldeep Tripathi holds over 16 years of experience in Marketing, Social Research, and Strategy Formulation along with “CSR and Sustainability”. He has worked as Head-CSR with NGOs on CSR Projects related to Health, Education, Environment, Water and Sanitation, etc). Currently, Kuldeep is heading the CSR division of PruVisor Management Consulting which provides strategic management services to Corporates & NGOs to develop impactful CSR initiatives. He is also heading as a Director-CSR (Honorary) at the International Council of Technology Management and Applied Engineering (ICTMAE), affiliated with CASI Global, New York (Global Certification body for CSR and Sustainability).
In the Round 1 of the event, the participants chose a problem statement of their choice solving a social problem or aimed to achieve one or more of the 17 Sustainable Development Goals defined by the United Nations.
They prepared an entire business plan and business model of the product right from the start till the end. The Plan consisted of core points such as the Problem Statement, Solution Overview, Revenue Model, Key Features, etc and the final presentation was to upload and submitted via a google form provided by us before 8 pm. Post detailed perusal top 7 teams were selected for the Round 2 of the event.

Round 2 - 16th April 2022
In the second round of the event, the selected teams were given a myriad of problem statements based on real problems faced by social entrepreneurs and social entrepreneurship projects.
Each team was then given exactly 30 minutes to come up with a solution to the problem that they presented to the judges and engaged in interesting and erudite conversations surrounding crucial aspects of entrepreneurship.
This was a one-on-one round with the judges and was held turn by turn. Every team was sent their problem statement and was given exactly 30 minutes before they’d have to present it to the judges.
The first problem statement was sent out at 12:20 pm and the presentations started at 1:00 pm where the rules of the competition were explained.
The presentations were evaluated based on the following criteria:
- Solution
- Business model
- Implementation
- Problem stats and impact of the solution
- Beneficiaries
Each Q&A round lasted for approximately 15 minutes where the judges asked them questions about various aspects of their business model such as sourcing of materials, logistics, finances, etc.
Round 2 Judges -
- Srishti Sharma - Serial entrepreneuhttps://www.bloomboxkjsce.com/admin/bb_app/events/add/#r and a social activist Founder at GAME
- Madhavi Jha Prasad - Social entrepreneur Founder- Aahanaa heritage foundation

fields.description: The session was conducted by Aditya Save(Co-Founder of Agilio Labs). Mr Aditya focused on the most important questions an entrepreneur needs to ask himself/herself. The reason behind the start up is the primary foundation of a successful business venture.
fields.details:
Aditya Save is a Mathematics graduate & holds a Masters degree in Marketing. He is currently pursuing a Doctoral course in Business Administration (DBA) from WestCliff University in California. The seminar was conducted to provi de students insight into the basics of starting up as an entrepreneur and a lso provide them with a platform to seek advice from our guest speaker.

Mr Aditya focused on the most important questions an entrepreneur needs to ask himself/herself. The reason behind the start up is the primary foundation of a successful business venture. The target population and the necessity of the product is equally important. Basically we need to have a meaningful answer to the ‘why’ aspect of our business model.

Once that is done, we need to do extensive research and acquire a basic knowledge of economics, math, psychology and taxation. Life isn’t about regretting the decisions that went wrong, it’s about learning from those mistakes and emerging stronger than before.

 2. Mr. Abhishek Rana – Founder of Codenera 
3. Mr. Prateek Jain – Inception program community manager at NVIDIA 

With the help of our sponsors, we had prizes worth up to Rs.30,000 for the winners and certificates. The winners of the event were announced at the end of the E-Summit in the Closing ceremony. All the participants have learned from the mistakes of the once-successful business, and they have gotten an opportunity to sharpen their skills of critical thinking and analysis.

fields.description: A Digital Marketing Event (or a Social Media Marketing Contest) was conducted during Abhiyantriki, annual technical festival of KJSCE.
fields.details:
A Digital Marketing Event (or a Social Media Marketing Contest) was conducted during Abhiyantriki, annual technical festival of KJSCE. Participants had to upload a video on any social media platform possible, and to win this competition, they were required to digitally market the video.

There was an interactive Question and Answer session taken by a famous Spoken Word Poet, Mr. Yahya Bootwala who entertained all the questions asked by the audience. Also, There was a speaker session by Mr. Chirag Warty who shared his expertise on Digital Marketing. The winning team was announced during our event ‘Entrepreneurship Day 2018.

fields.description: The session was conducted by Neha Chatterjee (Founder, Wopreneur) who is currently driving a community of 6000+ women entrepreneurs. Wopreneur is an organization to facilitate the growth of women.
fields.details:
The session was conducted by Neha Chatterjee (Founder, Wopreneur) who is currently driving a community of 6000+ women entrepreneurs Wopreneur is an organization to facilitate the growth of women in their chosen field and help them reach their potential

The session started with the life story of the speaker who was brought up in a middle class family, seeing domestic violence against women in the society, she grew up with the dream to change the system. She also spoke about her previous career as an investment banker in London then battling with cancer, heart attack and stroke.

The session was an interactive one and many points were discussed with the students like the limitations faced by women start-ups, ecosystem required to help them realize their potential and so on.

fields.description: Womenpreneur: is a virtual speaker session where the speaker will walk the audience through her journey in Entrepreneurship, the difficulties faced, how they overcame them and advice for young budding female Entrepreneurs.
fields.details:
All of us have been told about women empowerment and women in entrepreneurship but, how many of us have seen or experienced it being implemented on a first-hand basis? A very few…and hence wanting to inspire and encourage as well as educate students about entrepreneurship we had arranged a speaker session on 26th February at 4 pm using Google meet as the platform with 60+ participants. The purpose of this session was to help all the aspiring Womenpreneurs in their way towards success!  
The speaker for the session is none other than the eminent Entrepreneur Mrs. Amishi  Parasrampuria. She is a TEDx Speaker, NAAEE 30 Under 30, Founder at Upcycler's Lab,  Global Shaper, and a Sustainability Consultant. She guided the audience through her journey in Entrepreneurship, the difficulties she faced, how she overcame them, and advice for fellow young budding female Entrepreneurs.  

The meeting started with a discussion about Amishi Ma’am’s Entrepreneurial journey and how her  Never give up attitude helped her conquer various upcoming challenges. She further walked us through the process of forming her BoTo project with Global Shapers and founding Upcycler's  Lab. Moving on she shared about the amazing experiences she had in this journey like in particular she shared her wonderful experience at the World Trade Fair and how she got a  Successful response on her first visit itself.  

Later, Amishi Ma’am shared her views on the Impact of Shark Tank India amidst the Entrepreneurship  Boom phase. Further answering questions, she shared her insights on the Importance of Networking and Ways to start with it. She also emphasized the importance of listening to  Podcasts and Reading Books and shared her recommendations about them.  
For all the aspiring entrepreneurs in particular out there, this was an amazing opportunity to gain special and useful insights into the world of entrepreneurship through a woman's eyes.

pk: Zero to Hero - A Success Story

fields.description: BloomBox had Mr. Dhruvam Thakkar, Founder of The Smart Taxi to motivated the participants of E-Summit. Mr. Dhruvam shared his story and told us about how he struggled and gave his everything to make his dream come true.
fields.details: A good Speaker shares relevant information and facts, but a Great Speaker Shares a Story, an Emotion engaging the Crowd to the end which is why BloomBox had Mr. Dhruvam Thakkar, Founder of The Smart Taxi to motivate the attendees of the E-Summit. The speaker session was conducted on zoom on the 25th of April at 11:00 am and got 100+ participants from not just KJSCE but from all over India. Mr. Dhruvam shared his story and told us about how he struggled and gave his everything to make his dream come true. He drove taxis by himself in The Smart Taxi’s initial years and motivated the crowd by telling how he’s fearlessly competing with the giants in the space. The speaker session lasted for more than an hour throughout which Mr. Dhruvam was patient enough to answer every doubt asked. He encouraged people to follow their dreams irrespective of the conditions and made people learn the importance of hard-work and sheer dedication through his inspiring story.

pk: Zero to One ft. Raj Shamani

fields.description: Engaging us with an informative speaker session, we will have Mr. Shamani delivering his ideas and carrying us through various areas like Personal Branding, building Businesses, raising Funds for Start-ups and Student Entrepreneurship. Don’t forget to catch our speaker live and get a chance to interact with him and get your own entrepreneurial doubts cleared at our session.
fields.details:
BloomBox, E-Cell KJSCE is very excited to bring to you all the esteemed entrepreneur and keynote speaker- Mr. Raj Shamani!!! Mr. Shamani is a renowned content creator and a social media influencer with 1.2 M followers on Instagram and 518k subscribers on YouTube. He is highly regarded for his early-stage start-up investments and he is also the creator of an inspiring podcast “Figuring Out” that has forced its listeners to challenge themselves and do better at every turn. 
Engaging us with an informative speaker session, we will have Mr. Shamani delivering his ideas and carrying us through various areas like Personal Branding, building Businesses, raising Funds for Start-ups and Student Entrepreneurship. Don’t forget to catch our speaker live and get a chance to interact with him and get your own entrepreneurial doubts cleared at our session.
